content.description: Short and overhanging, there are anchors up top to protect you, this is more of a boulder problem but I put the bolts above in to do some explore other things and left them as they protect climbing on this face as well.
content.location: When you come in from the trail this will be on the right and will be the first all you come to, as you walk down a little more you will find the dihedral with Been Jammin and Mick Ray.

content.description: This is going to be on the right face of the dihedral, it has been done on top rope only but somebody is more than welcome to add bolts if they so desire.
content.protection: Trad, you would need to build your anchors.

content.description: There are anchors on this route and you can get to them by dropping in from two anchors at the top of the area.
content.location: This on on the eastern of the two areas.

content.description: Fun, low angle with easy climbing.
content.protection: There are bolts up top, to avoid the large chunk of rock that isn't going to move but I wasn't comfortable bolting I had to put the bolts higher than I would have liked so you will need something to extend them if you want to use them for protection.
content.location: This is on the left side of the dihedral.

content.description: I will be updating this over the next week to add more info and pictures.  Basically this is a small craig, short routes, quick and easy access and plenty of room for more development.  I love exploring so I found the area, put up a few routes and some anchors and I'm not going to do anything else with it but at least want it posted in case somebody else would like to enjoy it or add to it.
